{"lemma":"أُسْتاذٌ","slug":"أُسْتاذٌ","root":"#.س.ت.ذ","root_slug":"_-س-ت-ذ","root_link":"/words/roots/_-س-ت-ذ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n727"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B0%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"professor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"teacher at a grammar school or similar institution"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"title of courtesy commonly given to individuals of high education or learning, best translated simply as mister"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Classical Persian استاذ (ustād)."},"ipa":["/ʔus.taːð/","/ʔus.taːz/","/ʔus.taːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n727","headword_ar":"اُسْتَاذٌ","root":"AstA*","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a foreign word, pronounced to be such because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*","text_ar":"ذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"do not occur in any one Arabic word, (Msb,) not found in the poetry of the pagan times, (Ibn-Dihyeh in TA art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"st*","text_ar":"ستذ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) nor in the language of those times, (Shifá el-Ghaleel, ibid.,) [arabicized from the Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usotaAdo","text_ar":"اُسْتَادْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A master:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a skilful man, who is held in high estimation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a preceptor; a tutor; a teacher: a craftmaster:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Dihyeh; and Golius on the authority of Meyd:) [and so in the present day; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usotaA","text_ar":"اُسْتَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usoTaA","text_ar":"اُسْطَا"},{"kind":"text","text":":] also applied by the vulgar to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a eunuch;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because he generally tutors children: (Shifá el-Ghaleel, and Ibn-Dihyeh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usotaA*uwna","text_ar":"اُسْتَاذُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 377) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAtiy*u","text_ar":"اَسَاتِيذُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAti*apN","text_ar":"اَسَاتِذَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and vulgarly, in the present day,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usotawaAtN","text_ar":"اُسْتَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usoTawaAtN","text_ar":"اُسْطَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."}],"source_refs":["Msb","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}